PRNT (50% inhibition) were performed for the four serotypes during the same experiment in order to allow comparisons to be made between Fab (purified Fab and Fab in periplasmic extract) and mAb and between serotypes. This experiment was preceded by preliminary experiments, whose results are in accordance with those given in Table 1
(data not shown). mAb concentration which neutralized serotype 1 (0.28 μg ml−1) (Fig. 2
) was lower than that neutralizing serotypes 2 and 3 (2.25 μg ml−1) and serotype 4 (>2.25 μg ml−1) (Table 1). Periplasmic extract without Fab did not show any neutralizing properties. Fab neutralization capacity could be estimated as 8 times (serotypes 1 and 2) to four times (serotype 3) and four times or less (serotype 4) lower than that of mAb 4E11.
